OL,6,F"It's profound. It's devastating. As I
OL,7,Fstepped through Catherine's medical
OL,8,Frecords and came across information, a
OL,9,Fpoint where she'd been written up for
OL,10,Fan operation which never occurred, it
OL,11,Fwas evident that, had that operation
OL,12,Foccurred, she would have been alive -
OL,13,Fwords are not enough to describe the
OL,14,Fimpact of that."
OL,16,FHe continued: "Catherine was
OL,17,Fwonderful. It was a complete honour
OL,18,Fand privilege she chose to journey
OL,19,Fthrough her life with me.
